n\nRun these as separate passes. Preserve behavior unless a specific bug is found.\n\n### 1. Deletion Pass\n\nLook for speculative generality:\n\n- one-use traits\n- one-use structs\n- generic helpers with only one real caller\n- parameters added for imagined future agents\n- fields that are always `None` or always the same value\n- comments that repeat the code\n\nDelete or inline when the call s\n[TRUNCATED]\nons. If a finding\nrequires a new framework, it is probably not a cleanup finding.\n\n### Step 4. Make Small Behavior-Preserving Edits\n\nEdit in small groups:\n\n1. deletion/inlining\n2. naming\n3. visibility tightening\n4. comment cleanup\n5. test cleanup\n\nRun `cargo fmt` after edits. Avoid mixing a behavior fix with broad cleanup\nunless the behavior fix is tiny and directly discovered by the cleanup.\n\n### Step 5. Run Verification\n\nRun:\n\n```text\ncargo fmt --check\ncargo test -p but-agentlog\ncargo check -p but --features agentlog\ncargo clippy -p but-agentlog --all-targets --no-deps\ncargo machete\n```\n\nIf dependencies did not change, `cargo machete` is still cheap and catches\ncleanup leftovers.\n\n### Step 6. Optional Second Review\n\nAfter edits, spawn one or two fresh subagents only if the diff is non-trivial.\n\nGood second-pass prompts:\n\n- \"Review only the cleanup diff. Did behavior accidentally change?\"\n- \"Look for new complexity introduced by the cleanup.\"\n- \"Check whether any tests became weaker or more implementation-coupled.\"\n\nAvoid repeating the full four-subagent review unless the cleanup touched many\nmodules. Re-review has diminishing returns.\n\n### Step 7. Summarize The Result\n\nThe final summary should say:\n\n- what was removed or clarified\n- whether behavior changed\n- what validation ran\n- any remaining deliberate POC tradeoffs\n\nDo not claim the crate is now \"future-proof.\" The point is that it is easier to\nchange later because it is smaller and clearer now.\n\n## Cursor Note\n\nDo not force Cursor into the current JSONL parser path. Cursor's normal chat\nhistory is local SQLite, and its documented portable flow is Markdown export.\nThat deserves a separate design pass later.\n\n## Validation Habit\n\nBefore and after cleanup, run the narrow checks:\n\n```text\ncargo fmt --check\ncargo test -p but-agentlog\ncargo check -p but --features agentlog\ncargo clippy -p but-agentlog --all-targets --no-deps\ncargo machete\n```\n\nFor behavior-neutral cleanup, the best result is boring: smaller code, clearer\nnames, and the same tests passing.\n","tool_name":null,"tool_input":null,"source_record":{"timestamp":"2026-05-07T21:00:09.556Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"function_call_output","call_id":"[REDACTED:entropy]"}}}